records.addlTxt: DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Satorious.  Defendant plead no contest to the charges. Court recited the charge and possible penalties on the count she plead to.  Defendant understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. She understood.  Defendant stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Find guilty of 2 counts of:   Fail/Cause Child to Attend School contrary to 118.15(1)(a).  State recommended:   Probation 1 year.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  S.V.H. must attend school each and every day without any unexcused absences or tardies for the 2017-2018 academic year and if available, attend summer school in 2018.  Defense recommended a fine and costs.  Paperwork filed with the court.  Court ordered the same sealed.  After reviewing that paperwork, State agreed with the defense.  State recommended CC only.  Court ordered:  CC only.  $886.00.    Court advised defendant of the DNA submission requirement.  Add to current payment plan.    Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.
